parameters: \N[3]'s waiting...
An intricately crafted organ.
It may be best to spare it of
your piano "skills."
As you look at the beautiful statue of Trailia, you
notice a \ii[2] sitting on the base of the statue.
You have no idea how it got there, but you pick
it up anyways.
A
These are the stories that the priest
reads during church. At least, that's
what you've heard...
Looks like a bunch of fairy tales.
CallEvent 7
Actor4
\p3This is quite the adventure, huh?
Actor4
\p3You know, it was just a couple
days ago that I was robbed in
a tent, trapped between the
Banditos and the forest.
Actor4
\p3If you and \N[2] hadn't decided
to stick around, I don't know
what would have happened.
Actor4
\p3So uh... thanks for that. I don't know
if I properly thanked at any point.
Actor4
\p3You know, \N[1]... you remind
me of someone. I had a friend
once. His name was...
Actor4
\p3His name was...
Actor4
Actor4
\p3My mind really does want to forget
what happened back then, huh?
What I remember is that the good
times usually involved this boy.
I'm sure you'll remember one day.
Hey, you need to let the past go.
I'm sure you'll remember one day.
Actor4
\p3You know what? You're right.
Actor4
\p3I know this is kind of cheesy, but I hope this journey
ends up being one of self-discovery. I know our main goal
is to save the world, but I still want to figure out
who I was, who I am, and who I'll become.
Actor4
\p3And never tell the others this... but
honestly, not being lonely for once is
great. I guess I really needed human
contact and just never realized.
Just remember that we're all in this together.
Just remember that we're all in this together.
Actor4
\p3Mhm. Sorry if I was harsh to you at any
point. I have real respect for you, \N[1].
Hey, you need to let the past go.
Actor4
\p3I guess... but cut me a bit of slack. Not
all of the past needs to be forgotten.
Actor4
\p3Wanting to forget everything is just...
ignorant. If I throw away everything that
made me who I am today, then who I am
today is nothing. That's a quote, right?
Sorry, didn't mean it like that.
Sorry, didn't mean it like that.
Actor4
\p3Yeah... it's fine, I guess.
Actor4
\p3Anyways, regarding this statue.
Actor4
\p3Beautiful, right? That's Trailia, the
goddess of adventure. She has been known
to guide many lost souls to safety.
Actor4
\p3We reach her through these statues. They're
all over the world, and it doesn't matter
where or when we pray... Trailia will always
be there as a guiding light.
Actor4
\p3It's especially important that we maintain
contact with Trailia now that \c[18]Apocalypse\c[0]
is rearing his ugly head again. She'll guide
us to victory, I'm sure of it.
Actor4
\p3She's been reluctant to tell anyone
very much information. For now, she
simply serves as a guide, a mentor.
Actor4
Actor4
Actor4
Actor4
\p3I have to be honest. I think there's
something wrong with all of this.
Actor4
\p3Trailia should be able to reach us
anywhere. If she's really watching
over us all the time, why can we
only reach her at these statues?
Actor4
\p3If she's really the goddess of adventure,
why do we need to find a town and go
inside a building just to pray?
Actor4
\p3It just doesn't make sense.
Actor4
\p3The Above... I've heard legends of it.
It's the plane of existence where the
gods that created the Overworld rest.
Actor4
\p3It should be linked perfectly with the
Overworld. The gods in the Above should
be able to reach us anywhere.
Actor4
\p3But if the only god we've heard from is
Trailia, and we can only speak with her
at these statues... this link must not
be damaged. No, beyond damaged.
Actor4
\p3The link between the Overworld and the
Above has been severed. Trailia's only
channel for reaching the Overworld is
these statues, and that's absolutely it.
Actor4
\p3Who could have done this? No... what
could have done this? To be honest...
I don't know.
Actor4
\p3Only Trailia could have the power to do
something like this, but why would she do
this? Leaving the Overworld on its own has
left it in a constant state of war.
Actor4
\p3It must have been Trailia... and she
must have done it to save the Above...
from something.
Actor4
\p3It's all so confusing, and just another
one of my crazy theories... but this one
makes the most sense.
Actor4
\p3This theory will not be repeated to
anyone, understood? It's just a
theory, after all...
Actor4
\p3Well, this was an interesting chat...
Thanks for listening, \N[1].
Actor4
\p3Let's have another talk like this at some point.
CallEvent 7
People2

you come to worship?
People2
\vilThe church is open to anyone
at any time, no schedule.
People3
\solIt's nice to take a break from fighting
monsters 24/7 and find solace in the
guidings of Trailia.
People3
\solEven though she is the goddess of
travelers, many forget that she is
also the goddess of life and death.
People3
\solAnd besides, being a soldier is sort
of like being a traveler, right?
People2
\vilSeeing the same people every day for
weeks on end while sailing gets really
tiring. It's nice to be on land and
see other people, finally.
People2
\vilThe church is the best place for this.
People from all walks of life come here.
